  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Establish the Project Steering Committee and set regular meeting pattern\r\n\t\r\n\t\tSupport 6 Drop-in-Centre (DIC): staff training and development plan based on need example; case management practice, outreach skills, referral network mapping & networking, child participation, etc\r\n\t\r\n\t\tResearch findings workshop and action planning to embed recommendations into practice\r\n\t\r\n\t\tApplication of a knowledge, attitude and behavioural practice tool (KABP) to DIC staff\r\n\t\r\n\t\tForm and establish an on-going working relationship with the various members of the Monitoring and Action Committee\r\n\t\r\n\t\tDevelopment of a specific advocacy strategy with assigned tasks and indicators\r\n\t\r\n\t\tApplication of the public advocacy campaign\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFacilitate the MAC’s visits to the entertainment sector and highlight the roles and exploitation of children\r\n\t\r\n\t\tFacilitate the MAC to articulate their position on how they will address children’s involvement in the entertainment sector and CSEC in particular"
    },
    "ne": null
  },
